# Cloudflare Pages headers. Buildless app with STABLE filenames (no content hashes), so a
# long browser TTL shadows new deploys with the cached old modules until it expires — worse
# here because the experience is embedded in a cross-origin <iframe>, so even a parent
# hard-refresh doesn't bust the iframe's cached subresources.
#
# NOTE: Pages `_headers` matches a LEADING `/*` splat (optionally with a suffix, e.g. `/*.js`),
# but a trailing `/dir/*` splat did NOT match here — `/js/*` left the whole module graph on the
# platform default (max-age=14400, the stale-deploy bug). So target by extension instead.

# JS + HTML: always revalidate (a tiny 304 via ETag when unchanged; new code picked up on the
# next load right after a deploy instead of being shadowed for hours).
/*.js
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate
/*.html
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate

# Large, rarely-changing media — cache a day. three.min.js is vendored (r128) and never changes,
# so keep it cached (declared last so it wins over /*.js) to avoid revalidating 600 KB on every
# startup; purge in the Cloudflare dashboard on the rare swap.
/*.webp
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=86400
/three.min.js
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=86400
